<HEAD>Come Friday, You'll Be Working for Yourself</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Today is ``Tax Freedom Day,'' the day the
average American taxpayer finishes paying off taxes.
   The Tax Foundation calculates the average American will have to
work 124 days this year _ the same as in 1987 and 1988 _ just to
pay federal, state and local taxes. Today is the 124th day of the
year.
   Tax Freedom Day has never fallen later in the year. This year's
date is also the same as in 1981, before President Reagan and
Congress agreed on a 23-percent across-the-board cut in individual
income tax rates.
   Economists for the foundation, a nonpartisan Washington research
group, say the value of that tax cut has been offset by more than a
dozen subsequent federal tax increases and by higher state and
local taxes caused partially by cuts in federal programs.
</TEXT>
