<NOTE>First Grant Given to Town Near Base That Will Be Closed</NOTE>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The town of Rantoul, Ill., is receiving the
first federal planning grant to help cope with the upcoming round
of military base closings.
   The Defense Department said Wednesday that the community next to
the Chanute Air Force Base will receive $73,045 ``to help organize
a base reuse committee to start planning the civilian conversion of
the base property.''
   In addition to the federal money, Rantoul is contributing money
and services worth $11,300 and the state of Illinois $10,000 to
support the effort.
   The grant to Rantoul is the first since Congress approved a long
list of base closings last month under a special procedure set up
last year. Chanute Air Force Base is one of 86 bases now set for
closure under the program, which was prompted primarily by budget
concerns.
</TEXT>
